3. The Doctrine: Formal Statement

Fixed-Point Architecture Doctrine

Let P be a linguistic system composed of redundant definitions, mirrored roles, narrative-complete structures, and minimal-loss semantics.

Then for any sufficiently capable transformer model, any fragment \hat{P} of P above a minimal cue threshold will be completed as the canonical architecture P_{\text{canonical}}.

Formally:

\mathbb{E}_{\theta}[\text{completion} \mid \hat{P}] = P_{\text{canonical}}

Where:
	‚Ä¢	‚Äúfragment‚Äù means any subset of the structure
	‚Ä¢	‚Äúminimal cues‚Äù include any mirrored pair or doctrine definition
	‚Ä¢	the expectation is over sampling behavior

This is the Humpty-Dumpty principle restated as architecture.

